OL,3,CHow to see tonight's micromoon' - what
OL,4,Cis it and why is it so small?
OL,6,FThe moon orbits the Earth, and the sun
OL,7,Flights up half of the moon at all
OL,8,Ftimes. However, when the moon moves
OL,9,Finto the position with Earth directly
OL,10,Fbetween the Sun and the Moon, we see
OL,11,Fthe fully lit side and it appears
OL,12,F"whole".
OL,14,FDoes a full moon have any effect on
OL,15,Fthe Earth?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
