OL,3,CHow to see tonight's micromoon' - what
OL,4,Cis it and why is it so small?
OL,6,FInterestingly, full moons (and also
OL,7,Fnew moons) tend to give us stronger
OL,8,Ftides because, simply put, the
OL,9,Fgravitational pull of the moon and the
OL,10,Fsun line up and reinforce each other
OL,11,F(like two people pulling in the same
OL,12,Fdirection rather than against each
OL,13,Fother).
OL,15,FThis creates "spring tides" (nothing
OL,16,Fto do with the season, but instead
OL,17,Fthis refers to rising up or "springing
OL,18,Fup") where the tides rise higher than
OL,19,Fusual.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/11
