OL,3,CHow to see tonight's micromoon' - what
OL,4,Cis it and why is it so small?
OL,6,FWhat is unusual about this full moon?
OL,7,FTonight's "Flower Moon" is actually a
OL,8,F"micromoon" as it will appear slightly
OL,9,Fsmaller and dimmer than usual.
OL,11,FThis is because the full moon happens
OL,12,Fwhen the moon is near its furthest
OL,13,Fpoint from Earth in its orbit.
OL,15,FRemember that the moon's journey
OL,16,Faround the Earth is not a perfect
OL,17,Fcircle, it's slightly oval.
OL,26,@pD@AOUpD@KO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/11
