OL,3,CHow to see tonight's micromoon' - what
OL,4,Cis it and why is it so small?
OL,6,FThis means that sometimes the moon is
OL,7,Fcloser to Earth - which makes it
OL,8,Fappear bigger (supermoon) and
OL,9,Fsometimes, like tonight, it's further
OL,10,Faway which makes it appear smaller
OL,11,F(micromoon).
OL,13,FHow many full moons do we get each
OL,14,Fyear?
OL,16,FWe get a full moon about once every
OL,17,F29.5 days - so roughly once a month
OL,18,F(we call this cycle the synodic
OL,19,Fmonth), but not perfectly aligned with
OL,20,Fcalendar months.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/11
