OL,3,CHow to see tonight's micromoon' - what
OL,4,Cis it and why is it so small?
OL,6,FMost months have one full moon but
OL,7,Foccasionally timing lines up so we get
OL,8,Ftwo full moons in one calendar month.
OL,10,FThis is what will happen this month
OL,11,Fand the second full moon on May 31 is
OL,12,Fcalled a "Blue Moon". So most years we
OL,13,Fget twelve full moons, but this year
OL,14,Fan extra one just happens to fit into
OL,15,Fa calendar year.
OL,17,FAre there any traditions or folklore
OL,18,Fconnected with this full moon?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
