OL,3,CHow to see tonight's micromoon' - what
OL,4,Cis it and why is it so small?
OL,6,FIn medieval England, May's full moon
OL,7,Fwas sometimes called the Milk Moon -
OL,8,Fperhaps because cows were producing
OL,9,Fplenty of milk again after winter and
OL,10,Fthus, this full moon symbolised
OL,11,Fnourishment, prosperity, and comfort
OL,12,Fafter the lean months.
OL,14,FIn fact, the Flower Moon or Milk Moon
OL,15,Fhas a surprisingly rich mix of
OL,16,Ffolklore from different cultures, most
OL,17,Fof it tied to growth, fertility, and
OL,18,Fthe turning point into early summer.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/11
