OL,3,CHow to see tonight's micromoon' - what
OL,4,Cis it and why is it so small?
OL,6,FFurther north and east, patchy cloud
OL,7,Fshould still enable sight of the
OL,8,FFlower Moon but the view will be less
OL,9,Fclear.
OL,11,FExperts advise to look east just after
OL,12,Fsunset away from city light pollution.
OL,13,FNo equipment needed but binoculars can
OL,14,Fmake it more detailed.
OL,16,FHere is a list of the remaining full
OL,17,Fmoons of 2026:
OL,19,FMay 31 ` Blue Moon
OL,21,FJun 29 ` Strawberry Moon
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/11
